Reproduction is the process by which new organisms are created. There are two main methods of reproduction: sexual reproduction and asexual reproduction. Sexual reproduction involves the fusion of two gametes, usually through sexual intercourse. Asexual reproduction involves the production of new organisms without the fusion of gametes.
